<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-02A7B545-044B-40A7-BFE4-FE15134FF359" version="1" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-02A7B545-044B-40A7-BFE4-FE15134FF359" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">Report a printer installation</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M148684-B19"><p class="- topic/p ">To continuously improve the printer quality levels, field feedback is collected. The standard working method for <ph class="- topic/ph " translate="no" varid="Adam">ADAM</ph> provides such "Installation feedback" in a structured and fast manner. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">An Installation can be reported as successful or not successful. If not successful, the standard Issue type options must be used to indicate in detail which issues were encountered. This feedback will initiate appropriate counter actions from HQ. The following sections describe the different scenarios in more detail. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="GUID-E2C5C008-64D5-41D5-B176-B4FADEB47935" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Report a successful printer installation</title><p class="- topic/p ">On the "Collect" screen: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The "Main reason" field shows "Installation". 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The "Issue type" is preconfigured as "Installation". 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The "Issue description" is an optional field and does not need to be filled out. 
</p></li></ul><fig id="GUID-4242E4E9-F3FF-4BB5-9AFA-17F2EBEBC6F8" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A2742E66-E788-45C3-9B8D-7864045DBF67-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A2742E66-E788-45C3-9B8D-7864045DBF67-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">On the "Repair &amp; Evaluate" screen: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Select the first option: "Installation completed without issues". 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Click Exit and save the visit. 
</p></li></ul><fig id="GUID-41854B80-8ACD-428B-B209-1F707B3DEEF5" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-E3C27826-3F38-4E38-BCDB-F1AA78544065-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E3C27826-3F38-4E38-BCDB-F1AA78544065-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="M148684-B20" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Report an unsuccessful installation</title><p class="- topic/p ">On the "Collect" screen: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The "Main reason" field shows "Installation". 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The "Issue type" is preconfigured as "Installation". 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Add additional issues with the Issue-buttons and fill out in the Issue description field which issues were encountered during installation. 
</p></li></ul><fig id="GUID-0717BA0C-A2C6-4464-9740-6C8D0A8A4C21" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D228411E-09E6-491A-A816-9B623497502A-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D228411E-09E6-491A-A816-9B623497502A-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">On the "Repair &amp; Evaluate" screen: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Select the first option: "Installation completed but with issues". 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Process each of the issues in detail. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Click Exit and save the visit. 
</p></li></ul><fig id="GUID-C38F60E3-0A64-47C5-B42E-3E82C1770C75" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-569438E7-15AC-4968-91E9-546D2B86988A-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-569438E7-15AC-4968-91E9-546D2B86988A-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-8DB6EF7E-BEAA-4AAF-BA92-D6D60969DF00" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-591627EE-77C2-4F46-826B-7EA67C530DC3-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-591627EE-77C2-4F46-826B-7EA67C530DC3-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-8A03087D-4793-4CF6-87A0-E1C1B3DCAFB6" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Report a partial installation</title><p class="- topic/p ">A partial installation is typically reported if the installation takes more than one day. On the "Collect" screen: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The "Main reason" field shows "Installation". 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The "Issue type" is preconfigured as "Installation". 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The "Issue description" is an optional field and does not need to be filled out. 
</p></li></ul><fig id="GUID-F2FA27CD-D840-4737-91AE-1810005D226F" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A2742E66-E788-45C3-9B8D-7864045DBF67-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A2742E66-E788-45C3-9B8D-7864045DBF67-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">On the "Repair &amp; Evaluate" screen: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Select the first option: "Installation not completed, to be continued". 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Click Exit and save the visit. 
</p></li></ul><fig id="GUID-6E37B7C5-CE76-4890-A3E0-98F468EA1BA3" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6599A1DA-3CC6-44B5-B724-13C81362969C-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6599A1DA-3CC6-44B5-B724-13C81362969C-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Start <ph varid="Adam" translate="no" class="- topic/ph ">ADAM</ph> when the installation continues, for example on the next day. On the "Collect" screen: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Select the option "Second visit" as the "Main reason" (this is the only option at this point). 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Select "Installation" as the issue type that requires follow-up. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Click "Add" in the popup. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Continue the workflow as described above. 
</p><note id="GUID-F4A9BF89-31C1-408B-9431-B3ACFE0AF198" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">You will again have the same three installation options available at the end of the visit. 
</p></note></li></ul><fig id="GUID-51A7B7A0-17EF-4970-A600-4E1E7800F928" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C853CF80-1A3F-47AB-842E-7A6D74EDD1C8-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C853CF80-1A3F-47AB-842E-7A6D74EDD1C8-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-E79AA723-DF7D-47C9-87FA-CBE3B681763E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-3D2E74BE-5D09-4183-9942-2EBAC08B5B7F-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-3D2E74BE-5D09-4183-9942-2EBAC08B5B7F-low.png"/></fig></section></conbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="GUID-BA1FBADB-B384-4566-94B0-5A2D78B68783.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot gentext?>Collect</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
